  "texts": [
    "For the class label the ones with COVID positive is marked as 1 while the remaining are marked as negative (0).After that, the model goes through a pre-processing phase.",
    "During this stage a convolution with 30 filters with a size (5,5) is remained constant throughout the training stage (ie, the layer is not trainable).",
    "Next, the convolutional layers are formatted as follows: padding, strides (1, 1), 30 filters (described below), and 3TanH activation function [10].Next, SRM filters from YE-Net [31] are used, which are used to to pre-process our images [10].",
    "These filters are very much capable of extracting useful features from our CXR images.",
    "There are 8 \"Class I\", 4 \"Class II\" and 8 \"Class III\" filters."
  ],
